fields.name: Materials & Components
fields.description: This category encompasses basic raw materials, parts, or components required for manufacturing. It could be anything from steel beams to microchips, depending on the product being manufactured.

fields.name: Machinery & Equipment
fields.description: Essential machines or equipment required for specific tasks, whether it's about them being operational, calibrated, or installed.

fields.name: Technical Specifications
fields.description: Necessary technical details, drawings, or design specifications needed before a manufacturing process can start.

fields.name: Quality & Compliance
fields.description: This merges quality checks and regulatory requirements. It can refer to internal quality checks or external regulations and certifications that need to be met.

fields.name: Logistics & Suppliers
fields.description: Challenges or dependencies related to supply chain, including transportation, supplier delays, and other logistical concerns.
